    <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">The virtual machine image is based on CernVM (cernvm.cern.ch), with Scientific Linux CERN 6 (slc6), which is the environment needed for the CMSSW release
      to be used with the 2011 CMS open data. It gets the CMS software (CMSSW) from /cvmfs/cms.cern.ch and the jobs running on the CMS open data VM read the condition data from /cvmfs/cms-opendata-conddb.cern.ch. Access to the data is through XRootD.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="556" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">For known issues and limitations see</subfield>
      <subfield code="u">/VM/CMS#2011</subfield>
      <subfield code="y">CMS Virtual Machines - Known Issues and Limitations</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="567" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">The contextualisation scripts used for setting up the CMS VM images are available at</subfield>
      <subfield code="w">251</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="581" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Please follow the tutorial on how to use the CMS Virtual Machine</subfield>
      <subfield code="u">/VM/CMS#how</subfield>
      <subfield code="y">CMS Virtual Machines: How to install</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="583" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">A validation report of the CMS VM can be found at</subfield>
      <subfield code="u">/VM/CMS/validation/report#2011</subfield>
      <subfield code="y">Testing the CernVM</subfield>
    </datafield>
